  <paragraphs>
    <title>Post-video reflection</title>
    <p>
      Think about all the common functions you can name, such as <m>tan(x)</m>. Where are each of them continuous?
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

  <paragraphs>
   <title>Video 2: Continuity of Piecewise Functions</title>
    <p>
      When our functions are piecewise defined, we need to be particularly careful about checking continuity at the point where the definition changes.  </p>
